         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">14/8/88 ¶  ¶ I write this still from the bed, ¶  dear Madam and thus left your sympathetic letter ¶  so long unanswered. The wounds on my head are healed, but the foot still requires rest. It was so k...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">88.08.14</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Amy Beal</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Australian Manuscripts Collection, State Library of Victoria, Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">14/8/88</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I write this still from the bed,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">On 31 July 1888 M fell while alighting from a tram and injured his face and left knee-cap (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">Transactions of the Royal Geographical Society of Australasia (Victorian Branch)</seg>, part II, vol. vi, p. 13); see also M to T. Wilson, 1 August 1888.</p>
               </note> dear Madam and thus left your sympathetic letter<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Letter not found.</p>
               </note> so long unanswered. The wounds on my head are healed, but the foot still requires rest. It was so kind of you all to think of me with so much friendliness.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See also M to A. Beal, 21 November 1888 (in this edition as 88-11-21a).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A new work on <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Acacias of Australia</hi>
               </seg> has appeared just now, 13 decades with 130 plates.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B87.13.04 [Decades 1-7], B88.13.01 [Decades 8-13].</p>
               </note> — I have no doubt, if Miss Beal, as hon. Secr of your local Library,<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">i.e. at Lorne, Vic.</p>
               </note> did write to the hon the Premier for a copy, it would be granted. In a few weeks will also appear the completing volume of the "Key to the System of Victorian plants"<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B88.11.02.</p>
               </note> and the 7th Edition of the "Select plants (revised and enlarged),<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B88.12.01.</p>
               </note> which should prove acceptable also there.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With regardful your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">You are sure to come when the weather gets warmer to the Exhibition.<note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Centennial International Exhibition, Melbourne, 1888-9.</p>
               </note> Excuse me for writing no more; it is so difficult for me yet.</p>
         </div>
